wiki.content: “Hellcats & Trackhawks” is a standout track off of Loyal Bros. Only The Family’s label boss Lil Durk delves into the consequences of rap beef and drug usage over a Nick Slowburnz-produced instrumental. The title of the song refers to two high-performance cars, the Dodge Challenger SRT Hellcat and Jeep Grand Cherokee Trackhawk. The official music video for the song premiered exactly three weeks after its release, March 26, 2021. Like the visuals of “Backdoor” and “Back in Blood,” the latter being a Pooh Shiesty song that Lil Durk appears on, the Chicago rapper flexes and pays tribute to his OTF artist and close friend King Von, who passed away after being shot outside of a nightclub in Atlanta, Georgia, on November 6, 2020.
